      <br><br>What users want from data is insights. Insight is gained when knowledge interacts with knowledge: therefore,
      data should flow freely throughout systems, rather than being stored in ‘data silos’.
      <br><br>
      That is why we prefer to work with semantically structured data models, which allow for data reusability, seamless
      integration, easy sharing, and automatic enrichment. In short, more insight, less waste.
      <br><br>
