          <h4 class="values-item-title ">Open source</h4>
          <p class="values-item-text">We consider ourselves an Open source company. Whenever possible we prefer to use
            Open
            Source, we contribute to open source projects, and we publish our work under open source
            licenses when we can.
          </p>

      </li>
      <li class="values-list-item">

          <h4 class="values-item-title ">Open standards</h4>
          <p class="values-item-text">We prefer not to publish data using proprietary standards, as we think this is
            often
            inefficient.
            By instead adopting open standards and semantics, we make our data more powerful and interoperable.</p>

      </li>
      <li class="values-list-item">

          <h4 class="values-item-title ">Distributed solutions</h4>
          <p class="values-item-text">Too often, web services and applications rely on a single point of failure.
            By switching to decentralized models, we make our products faster and more reliable. </p>

      </li>
      <li class="values-list-item">

          <h4 class="values-item-title ">Research</h4>
